   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Grammar and Style Improver\\n\",\"**NLP Project 50 of 100** — Rewrite text for clarity and concision using rule-based checks and LLMs.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import re, requests\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Rule-based style improvements\\ndef improve_style(text):\\n    improvements = []\\n    # Passive voice detection (simple heuristic)\\n    if re.search(r'\\\\b(was|were|been|being)\\\\s+\\\\w+ed\\\\b', text):\\n        improvements.append('Consider active voice instead of passive.')\\n    # Wordy phrases\\n    wordy = {'in order to':'to','due to the fact that':'because','at this point in time':'now',\\n             'in the event that':'if','for the purpose of':'to','in spite of the fact that':'although'}\\n    cleaned = text\\n    for phrase, replacement in wordy.items():\\n        if phrase in text.lower():\\n            cleaned = re.sub(re.escape(phrase), replacement, cleaned, flags=re.IGNORECASE)\\n            improvements.append(f'Replaced \\\"{phrase}\\\" → \\\"{replacement}\\\"')\\n    # Sentence length check\\n    sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', text)\\n    long = [s for s in sentences if len(s.split()) > 25]\\n    if long: improvements.append(f'{len(long)} sentence(s) are too long (>25 words). Consider splitting.')\\n    return cleaned, improvements\\n\\ntests = [\\n    'In order to improve our results, we need to increase the sample size due to the fact that it is too small.',\\n    'The report was written by the analyst. At this point in time, we should review it.',\\n    'The data was processed and the model was trained using a complex pipeline that includes multiple steps of feature engineering and hyperparameter optimization and cross validation.',\\n]\\n\\nfor text in tests:\\n    cleaned, notes = improve_style(text)\\n    print(f'Original:  {text}')\\n    print(f'Improved:  {cleaned}')\\n    for n in notes: print(f'  💡 {n}')\\n    print()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# LLM-based improvement\\ndef llm_improve(text, model='qwen3:1.7b'):\\n    prompt = f'Rewrite this text for clarity and concision. Fix grammar, reduce wordiness, prefer active voice. Output only the improved text.\\\\n\\\\nText: {text} /no_think'\\n    try:\\n        r = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate',json={'model':model,'prompt':prompt,'stream':False},timeout=60)\\n        return r.json().get('response',text)\\n    except: return text\\n\\nprint('LLM-improved:')\\nprint(llm_improve(tests[0]))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Rule-based checks catch common wordiness** and passive voice.\\n\",\"- **LLMs provide more nuanced rewriting.**\\n\",\"- **Combine both for comprehensive style improvement.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
